        </div>

        <div class="row locrow">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                <img src="~/Content/Images/M-02_Wailua_Falls_web-LG_large.jpg" class="img-thumbnail img-responsize moveright" alt="Hawaiian surfer" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                <section>
                    <h2>Maui</h2>
                    <h4>The Valley Isle</h4>
                    <p>Maui is 727 square miles, making it the second largest island. Maui is most notable for its mountain ranges and valleys, and is often called the Valley Isle. It is the second most popular tourist destination in the state. While visiting Maui, make time to see the Kaanapali and Wailea resort areas and Haleakala, the largest dormant volcano crater in the world.</p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row locrow">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                <section class="moveup">
                    <h2>Oahu</h2>
                    <h4>The Gathering Place</h4>
                    <p>Oahu is by far the most popular destination among tourists, attracting nearly twice as many visitors as Maui each year. It is the third largest Hawaiian island, with 597 square miles. It is also the most populated, and home to the capital, Honolulu. Must-sees during your stay include Waikiki and Pearl Harbor.</p>
                </section>
